NIL Connection

2023-24

CSC Academic All-District… Academic All-MAC… Played in 33 games, making five starts… Shooting percentage of .487 (76-for-156)… Averaged 5.9 points per game and 3.5 rebounds per game… Added 24 assists, 15 steals and seven blocks… Opened season with 11 points on 5-of-9 shooting at James Madison (Nov. 8)… Three steals each against Gonzaga (Nov. 12) and SMU (Nov. 24)… Grabbed 10 rebounds in neutral-site win vs. North Dakota State (Nov. 25)… Totaled 11 points, grabbed eight rebounds in win vs. Northern Illinois (Jan. 24)… Put up season-high 12 points in 11 minutes played at Akron (Jan. 31)… Totaled 10 points, six rebounds vs. Ball State (Feb. 24)… Four double-digit scoring games… Eight games with five or more rebounds… Six multi-assist games.

2022-23

CSC Academic All-District…Academic All-MAC…MAC All-Tournament Team; scored 16 points, grabbed seven rebounds in title game vs. Bowling Green…Played in 33 games, starting 30…Averaged 6.8 PPG, 3.9 RPG…10 double-digit scoring performances…Tallied a double-double in season opener vs. Wright State, scoring 19 points and grabbing 10 rebounds (Nov. 7)…13 points at Cincinnati (Nov. 16)…Went 5-for-5 from the floor and scored 12 points vs. UT Arlington (Nov. 26)…Scored 14 points and made all seven field goal attempts vs. Akron (Jan. 21)…12 points, went 5-fot-6 from the floor vs. Miami (Jan. 25)…11 points, tied season-high with three assists vs. Buffalo (Feb. 8)…Tallied 12 points at Western Michigan (Feb. 15)…Scored 16 points on 8-of-11 shooting , tallied seven rebounds vs. Bowling Green in MAC Tournament Championship Game (March 12).

2021-22

MAC All-Freshman Team…Played in 33 games, starting 25…Averaged 8.2 PPG and 5.5 RPG…Ranked seventh in the MAC in offensive rebounds per game (2.82)…Began her collegiate career with double-doubles in her first two games; was one of 12 players in the Division I ranks to have two double-doubles in the season’s first two games, and one of just two freshmen to achieve that feat (Rheme Ogele, Portland State)…Became first Rocket since 2018-19 to have double-doubles in back-to-back games (Kaayla McIntyre)…Scored 16 points and grabbed 11 rebounds in first collegiate game at Oakland (Nov. 9)…Followed that up with 19 points and 12 boards against Wright State (Nov. 13)…Scored eight points and collected six rebounds against Idaho State in Cancun Challenge (Nov. 25)…Scored 11 points and hauled in seven rebounds at Northern Illinois (Jan. 15)…Scored in double figures in four straight games from Jan. 22-Feb. 2, including tying a season-high with 19 points against Ohio (Jan. 26)…Season-best 13 rebounds at Bowling Green (Jan. 29), also scored 10 points for third double-double of the year…10 points and eight rebounds in win at Miami (Feb. 9)…Scored 12 points and added nine rebounds at home against BGSU (Feb. 12)…Back-to-back games scoring in double figures at EMU (12 points, Feb. 26) and against Northern Illinois (14 points, March 2)…Scored eight points and grabbed 10 rebounds in MAC Tournament win against Ohio (March 9)…13 points in WNIT win against Houston Baptist.

High School

Averaged 20.8 points and 12.6 rebounds per game as a junior at Cicero-North Syracuse High School in 2019-20…Helped the Northstars capture a Section III, Class AA championship as a junior…Scored at least 20 points on 14 occasions as a junior, including a season-high 38 against Liverpool (Jan. 3), en route to earning All-Central New York High School Player of the Year honors…First-team all-state large schools according to the New York State Sportswriters Association (NYSSWA) and named to the Syracuse.com All-CNY first team.
